Yes — there are a few more options worth adding now, but I would avoid adding every possible Kickstart option. The goal should be: add options that are likely to become real profile choices, not options just because Kickstart supports them.

Also, one important thing: since Kickstart syntax and support can differ by RHEL major version, especially RHEL 7 versus RHEL 8/9/10, I would keep the partials simple and use os_major conditionals only where needed. Red Hat keeps separate Kickstart references for RHEL 10 and RHEL 9, and the RHEL 9 docs specifically call out auth/authconfig as deprecated starting with RHEL 8, which is a good example of why we should be careful with cross-version partials.  ￼

The one structural change I would make now

I would split this:

90-security/
  selinux-enforcing-firewall-ssh.ks.j2

That combines too many different decisions into one file:

selinux
firewall
firewall ssh service

Better:

90-selinux/
  _meta.yml
  enforcing.ks.j2
  permissive.ks.j2
  disabled.ks.j2
95-firewall/
  _meta.yml
  enabled-ssh.ks.j2
  disabled.ks.j2

Then keep:

100-services/
  _meta.yml
  sshd-enabled.ks.j2

That will make the future override-builder much cleaner because someone can choose SELinux mode separately from firewall behavior.

