That is better than keeping 90-security because it avoids one partial doing three different jobs.

My recommendation

Add the extra files now, but mark anything not ready as status: placeholder in _meta.yml. Then the future helper script can hide or warn on placeholders.

For example:

title: Network configuration
required: true
selection: one
default: dhcp-link.ks.j2
description: Controls how the installed system configures networking during installation.
options:
  - file: dhcp-link.ks.j2
    label: DHCP on active link
    status: supported
  - file: dhcp-link-with-hostname-prompt.ks.j2
    label: DHCP with hostname prompt
    status: supported
  - file: dhcp-specific-device.ks.j2
    label: DHCP on a specific device
    status: supported
  - file: static-ip-placeholder.ks.j2
    label: Static IP
    status: placeholder

That gives you room to grow without accidentally presenting unfinished choices as production-ready.